'''''Beaky and the Egg Snatchers''''' is a ''[[Joust (video game)|Joust]]'' clone developed for the [[ZX Spectrum]] by Bob Hamilton and published by [[Fantasy Software]]. A [[Commodore 64]] version was published the same year.

== Gameplay ==
The player takes on the role of the last of the Andromdean Condors who must prevent their species from becoming extinct by rescuing them from the egg snatchers. The game plays similarly to Jetpack and Joust.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.retrogamer.net/retro_games80/beaky-and-the-egg-snatchers/|title=Beaky and the egg snatchers &#124; Retro Gamer|date=23 March 2010 }}</ref>

==Reception==
''Beaky and the Egg Snatchers'' was positively received, including two out of three approvals from ''[[Your Spectrum]]'' reviewers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.users.globalnet.co.uk/~jg27paw4/yr08/yr08_59.htm |title=Your Spectrum : Joystick Jury |date=October 1984 |publisher=Users.globalnet.co.uk |accessdate=2015-11-03}}</ref> It received a score of 31/40 from ''[[Computer & Video Games]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://archive.org/stream/cvg-magazine-033/CVG_033_Jul_1984#page/n43/mode/1up/ |title=CVG Magazine Issue 033 |date= July 1984|accessdate=2015-11-03}}</ref> and 34/50 from ''[[Personal Computer Games]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://archive.org/stream/Personal_Computer_Games_Issue10#page/n55/mode/2up |title=Personal Computer Games Issue10 |date= |accessdate=2015-11-03}}</ref>

